					<h1 class="border">SMS Messaging FAQ</h1>
					<h2>Do you charge for incoming text messages?</h2>
					<p>
No, we only charge for subscribers, so all text messages are free, whether they're going out or coming in.
					</p>
					<h2>How many characters can I include in a mass text message?</h2>
					<p>
In mass text messages you get 137 characters as by default we use 23 characters at the bottom of your text message to give instructions on how SMS subscribers are able to unsubscribe.
					</p>
					<h2>How many characters can I include in SMS Autoresponders?</h2>
					<p>
In SMS Autoresponders you get 160 characters.
					</p>
					<h2>How long does it take to deliver a text message?</h2>
					<p>
Most text messages will arrive on your subscribers mobile phones within a few seconds. The rumors are true, the movie The Fast and the Furious was created after after watching how fast Tatango text messages are sent.
					</p>
					<h2>Will you send advertisements via text message to my contacts?</h2>
					<p>
No. Never.
					</p>
					<h2>Can I choose what to send to my customers?</h2>
					<p>
You're actually the only person that can decide what your customers receive from your business. You control what to send and when to send it with your SMS campaign. Tatango puts the power in your hands.
					</p>
					<h2>Can I receive replies to my mass text messages?</h2>
					<p>
Yes, SMS subscribers are able to reply to any mass text message that you send them. These replies will be stored under the reports for each individual mass text messaging campaign.
					</p>
					<h2>Can I send mass messages from my mobile phone?</h2>
					<p>
Yea, we're innovative like that. The best part is that you don't need to download an app or have internet on your mobile phone, you just need to know how to text message.
					</p>
					<h2>What carriers does tatango work on?</h2>
					<p>
The better question is to ask what U.S. wireless carriers Tatango doesn't work on√â the answer is zero.
					</p>
					<h2>Can I customize the opt-in message SMS subscribers receive?</h2>
					<p>
Yep! With all of the legal stuff we have to include in an opt-in message, you're allowed 75 characters for customization. We call this opt-in message the "Reward Message" because the majority of Tatango customers use these available characters to give some kind of reward to their customers for joining their SMS campaign.
					</p>
					<h2>Does Tatango allow SMS subscribers to unsubscribe from mass messages?</h2>
					<p>
Any SMS subscriber that wants to leave your subscriber list has to simply respond to any text message they receive from your SMS campaign with the word "STOP" or "UNSUBSCRIBE". This happens automatically, so no need to worry about creating extra work for yourself.
					</p>
					<h2>Does Tatango do MMS?</h2>
